-- HIGHLIGHTS-Draghi comments at ECB news conference
-- 
-- Thu Aug 07, 2014 08:34AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, Aug 7 (Reuters) - The European Central Bank held borrowing rates on Thursday as it pinned its hopes on lending measures to bolster a struggling euro zone economy facing further damage from the Ukraine conflict.

Following are comments by ECB President Mario Draghi at a post-meeting news conference.  RATE OUTLOOK "ECB interest rates will remain at the current level for an extended period of time."